article.headline: Florida Atlantic 77, UMKC 59
article.story: BOCA RATON, Fla. -- Shavar Richardson scored 18 points and Florida Atlantic beat UMKC 77-59 on Saturday night. The Owls (3-1) are off to their best start in 20 years, improving their record to 3-1 for the first time in their 15-year Division I history. Xavier Perkins scored 17 points and grabbed seven rebounds for Florida Atlantic. Paul Graham III had 16 points and four assists. Reggie Hamilton scored 22 points to lead the Kangaroos (1-3). He also grabbed six rebounds and had five assists. Graham scored his first basket just 43 seconds into the game. The score by Graham made him the seventh player in Florida Atlantic history to have scored 1,000 points.
